0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 271 "3.  Fundamental The
orem of Algebra.  The Fundamental Theorem of Algebra asserts that ever
y non-constant polynomial (with complex-valued coefficients) has a roo
t (a zero, a solution).  A consequence of the Fundamental Theorem of A
lgebra is that every polynomial of degree " }{TEXT 270 1 "n" }{TEXT 
-1 13 " has exactly " }{TEXT 271 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 108 " roots.  An alte
rnate formulation of this consequence would be that every non-constant
 polynomial of degree " }{TEXT 273 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 38 " can be factore
d into a product of a  " }{TEXT 272 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 16 " linear factor
s." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 35 "Con
sider the following polynomials:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "I.    " }{MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "f := x^3-x^2-2*x
" }{TEXT -1 15 "         II.   " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "g := 6*x^3+11*x^2+6*x
+1" "6#>%\"gG,**&\"\"'\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"$F(F(*&\"#6F(*$F*\"\"#F(F(*&F'F
(F*F(F(F(F(" }{TEXT -1 24 "                 III.   " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "h
 := x^3-5*x+x^2-5;" "6#>%\"hG,**$%\"xG\"\"$\"\"\"*&\"\"&F)F'F)!\"\"*$F
'\"\"#F)F+F," }{TEXT -1 19 "                   " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 7 "IV.    " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "F := x^4-144" "6#>%\"FG,&*$%\"xG
\"\"%\"\"\"\"$W\"!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 19 "             V.    " }{XPPEDIT 
19 1 "G := 3*x^4+4*x^3-2*x^2+x-6;" "6#>%\"GG,,*&\"\"$\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"
%F(F(*&F+F(*$F*F'F(F(*&\"\"#F(*$F*F/F(!\"\"F*F(\"\"'F1" }{TEXT -1 15 "
         VI.   " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "H := x^5-x^2-2*x" "6#>%\"HG,(*$%\"xG
\"\"&\"\"\"*$F'\"\"#!\"\"*&F+F)F'F)F," }{TEXT -1 24 "                 \+
       " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 257 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
